<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>In Zend_Uri_Http.php, line 231, brackets surrounding an IPv6 are explicitly stripped.</p>

<p>The problem is, nothing puts them back when making the actual connection, leading to invalid ip:port combinations.  For example, it should be [::1]:80, but is instead ::1:80</p>

<p>To work around it for now, I patched Zend_Http_Client_Adapter_Socket.php to conditionally wrap the $host variable in brackets on lines 195 and 269.  I did it in a decidedly non-Zendy way, but it works.</p>

